ning\'caclose to 50 km per week for an average of }{\fs18\expnd0\expndtw-2 8}{\fs18\expnd0\expndtw-2  years. \par }{\*\cs73\fs18\b\i\expnd0\expndtw0\cf1\outl0
Task and Procedures:}{\f7\fs18\b\i  }{\fs18 Participants ran on a treadmill on two days. The first day involved establishing their baseline performance characteristics engaging them in a standard graded exercise test for a maximum of 20 }
{\fs18 min}{\fs18 . On the second day participants ran for 20 }{\fs18 min}{\fs18  on the treadmill at a speed equivalent to 75 percent of their maximum oxygen consumption, which had been }
{\fs18\expnd-1\expndtw-3 determined on day 1. Prior to and after the day 2 running \line }{\fs18 session, participants were given questionnaires asking them to rate the ease of their running.\par }
\pard\plain \s37\f6\fs18\ltrpar\qj\fi240\li0\ri0\sb0\sa0\tx240\facenter\sl220\slmult0\expnd0\expndtw0\cf1\up0\charscalex100\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\accnone\hyphpar1\lang1033
{\fs18 Two groups were formed on day 2. After running for 10 }{\fs18 min}{\fs18 , the }{\*\cs61\fs18\b0\i Enhanced Expectancy}{\fs18
 group received feedback about their oxygen consumption every 2 }{\fs18 min}{\fs18  \line for the duration of their run. They were told that their oxygen consumption was in the top 10 }
{\fs18 percentile}{\fs18  for their age and gender. The }{\*\cs61\fs18\b0\i Control}{\fs18  group was not given any feedback about their oxygen consumption while they ran.\par }
\pard\plain \s35\f6\fs18\ltrpar\qj\fi0\li0\ri0\sb120\sa0\tx240\facenter\sl220\slmult0\expnd0\expndtw0\cf1\up0\charscalex100\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\accnone\hyphpar1\lang1033
{\*\cs73\fs18\b\i\expnd0\expndtw0\cf1\outl0 Performance Evaluation:}{\fs18  Oxygen consumption, heart rate, and perceived exertion were measured for all participants.\par }
{\*\cs73\fs18\b\i\expnd0\expndtw-2\cf1\outl0 Results:}{\fs18\expnd0\expndtw-2  The primary result was that oxygen consumption rates were comparable between the two groups for the first 10 }
{\fs18\expnd0\expndtw-2 min}{\fs18\expnd0\expndtw-2  but then systematically decreased for the Enhanced Expectancy group for the remainder of the 20-}
{\fs18\expnd0\expndtw-2 min}{\fs18\expnd0\expndtw-2  running session. No change in oxygen consumption rate occurred for the Control group. \par }
